    <h1><u>Nepalease Foods</u></h1>

    <p>
        Nepalese food is known for being simple, healthy, and full of flavor. One of the most popular dishes is dal bhat, which
        includes rice, lentil soup, and vegetables, and is eaten daily by many people. Momos, which are dumplings filled with
        meat or vegetables, are also a favorite snack across the country. Nepalese cuisine is influenced by both Indian and
        Tibetan cultures, making it a unique mix of flavors. Food in Nepal is also about tradition, family, and sharing meals
        together.
    </p>

